name: G7 Residence Bali

review 1: The mobile phone number is not of the premises, please beware.. this number claimed to be the person incharge and will ask for deposit to be transferred. Where actually when you want to stay there the receptionist will give you the real bank account number.
review 2: Nice and clean with peaceful environment. Bali Tourism Polytechniques (Politeknik Pariwisata Bali) is just nexdoor. review 3:
Small room and very humid, damp...especially on the first floor. Leave your leather stuff for one day in this room and it will get moldy. Unstable internet connection. Unsafe - a thief stole my belongings here and there was nothing they can do.

name: Madawa Bali
address: Jalan Astina Pura Jl. Raya Kampial No.1, Benoa, Kec. Kuta Sel., Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80361, Indonesia
review 1: This place is a hidden gem, it's fine dining located in an area of Benoa one wouldn't expect. The building is what makes this place special, very photogenic. The food could have been better, however I haven't gotten the chance to try one of their signature dishes yet.
review 2:
My recent dining experience at Madawa Restaurant was nothing short of exceptional, marked by an exquisite blend of professional service and experience.

Staff Professionalism and Friendliness: The staff at Madawa struck a perfect balance between professionalism and warmth. Their attentive and friendly service created a welcoming atmosphere that added to the overall dining experience.

Quality of Service: The service was impeccable. From the moment we entered until our departure, every need was anticipated and met with efficiency and a smile. The staff's knowledge about the menu and their recommendations were particularly commendable.

Culinary Excellence: The quality of the dishes served at Madawa was a true highlight. Each dish was a testament to the chef's expertise, presenting a delightful array of flavors and textures. The presentation was as impressive as the taste, making each course a culinary delight.

Madawa Restaurant offers an outstanding dining experience where the quality of service matches the excellence of its cuisine. The staff‚Äôs dedication to ensuring a memorable meal is evident in every interaction. I highly recommend Madawa Restaurant to anyone seeking a dining experience that combines exceptional food with top-notch service of western and traditional local delights.
review 3:
Stayed at taman dharmawangsa villas for 5 nights. 4 of the days I just wanted to hole up and relax at the resort so I could just chill. Had lunch and dinner ever day at madawa and it was awesome. Service is great,
Cocktails super delicious, food was delicious and presentation was excellent. Restaurant was pretty busy at breakfast for the buffet (also excellent) but for some reason it‚Äôs really quiet during lunch and dinner. Which is such a shame because the restaurant is fantastic and the ambiance is just lively with piano music playing and an absolutely beautifully designed restaurant. If you‚Äôre staying at TD or staying nearby honestly I could not recommend you staying in and trying the hotel restaurant more.

review 1: Great hostel, provides everything you could wish for and more. The free dinner is super yum and a great concept as afterward there is a really social atmosphere with everyone hanging out :) Double Room is nice with own bathroom. One star less because of the distance to the famous surf beaches. Overall recommend!
review 2: Awesome staff! Very cool place! The owner is super super friendly. He organizes perfect party shuttles and many more exciting events! I would definetely recommend this hostel to everyone! The free dinners is just a cherry on top!‚ù§Ô∏è
review 3: Our stay at the hostel has just been great. The local people working here and the staff coming from outside had made our stay even better. The free dinner makes it a good place to feel comfortable. You meet people from every corner of the world - we will come back some day!
review 4: This place has a chill atmosphere, a daily shuttle to local places, and a free yummy dinner! Great place to meet people too! The beds are pretty private for a hostel and you have your own "box". Small cute pool and good showers!
review 5:
The hostel itself is correct. Located on a private little street, further from the city noise. The two dogs are super cute and friendly. The common area is good and the family dinner are really appreciated. The owner went out of his way for us vegetarian guests.

The room to the doors were broken and really hard to open which means, everytime someone went in or out, it woke up the dorm.

Hot showers, clean bathrooms but staff doesn't speak English so it's hard to communicate.
